history.content:
I was not quite sure how the swap process worked on CalCentral. Initially, during phase 2, I tried swapping EE 16B, which I was already enrolled in, with CS 61B, which already had a waitlist. I was consequently placed on the 61B waitlist while staying enrolled in 16B, under the condition that if I got off the waitlist for 61B, I would be dropped from 16B. However, I later dropped EE 16B myself, and during adjustment enrolled back in it but under a different lab section, while staying under the unit cap of 20.5 units inclusive of my 61B waitlist (4 other courses + 61B waitlist).

I'm now wondering if I will still be dropped from 16B if I get off the 61B waitlist? I plan on taking both this semester and I would like a heads up if I'm going to be booted off 16B 3 or 4 weeks in. Not sure if this is the best place to be asking, but if there's someone else I can contact that can help me figure this out, do let me know!
history.subject: Swapping classes and waitlists
